## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="e1705-119">携帯電話は、文字または音声のサウンドを表す記号です。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e1705-119">Phones are letters or symbols that describe the sounds of speech.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="e1705-120">System.Speech カスタム発音を指定する 3 つの phonetic アルファベットをサポートしています: ユニバーサル電話設定 (UPS)、Speech API (SAPI) 電話設定 で、および国際音声記号 (IPA)。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e1705-120">System.Speech supports three phonetic alphabets for specifying custom pronunciations: the Universal Phone Set (UPS), the Speech API (SAPI) Phone set, and the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="e1705-121">指定された電話<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A>で指定された発音記号に一致する必要があります<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsDocument.PhoneticAlphabet%2A>です。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e1705-121">The phones specified in <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> must match the phonetic alphabet specified in <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsDocument.PhoneticAlphabet%2A>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="e1705-122">参照してください[辞書と音声のアルファベット](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/435e3c6f-6834-4e5a-b0f6-c17b2275dc51)詳細についてはします。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e1705-122">See [Lexicons and Phonetic Alphabets](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/435e3c6f-6834-4e5a-b0f6-c17b2275dc51) for more information.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="e1705-123">指定された電話<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A>を示す方法の内容<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A>成功認識用に増大する必要があります。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e1705-123">The phones specified in <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> indicate how the contents of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A> should be pronounced for successful recognition.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="e1705-124">音声認識エンジンで指定された発音を使用して<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A>音声入力およびに含まれている文字列を返します。 一致する<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A>認識結果にします。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e1705-124">The speech recognition engine uses the pronunciation specified in <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> to match speech input and returns the string contained by <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A> in the recognition result.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="e1705-125">認識エンジンに含まれる、word の有効な発音として指定された発音を認識しない場合は、携帯電話がスペースで区切られたか、指定した文字列が認識されない電話を含む、<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A>です。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e1705-125">If the phones are not space-delimited or the specified string contains an unrecognized phone, the recognition engine does not recognize the specified pronunciation as a valid pronunciation of the word contained by <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="e1705-126">指定された発音<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A>文法または認識エンジンに関連付けられた辞書で指定された発音よりも優先されます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e1705-126">Pronunciations specified in <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> take precedence over pronunciations specified in lexicons associated with a grammar or a recognition engine.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="e1705-127">も、発音、<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A>プロパティに含まれる語句の 1 つにのみ適用される<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A>です。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e1705-127">Also, the pronunciation in the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> property applies only to the single occurrence of the word or phrase contained by <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A>.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="e1705-128">次の例では文法俗語単語が含まれています、一般的でない単語があります:"whatchamacallit"です。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e1705-128">The grammar in the following example contains slang words and also has an uncommon word: "whatchamacallit".</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="e1705-129">カスタム、インライン発音を使用して、追加する、<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A>のプロパティ、<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken>クラスは、"whatchamacallit"もそれを含む語句全体と word の認識の精度を向上させることができます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e1705-129">Adding a custom, inline pronunciation using the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> property of the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken> class can improve the accuracy of recognition for the word "whatchamacallit" as well as for the entire phrase that contains it.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="e1705-130">例では、携帯電話から、Microsoft Universal 電話設定 (UPS) を使用して、カスタム発音を定義します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e1705-130">The example uses phones from the Microsoft Universal Phone Set (UPS) to define the custom pronunciations.</span></span>  
  
```  
using System;  
using System.Speech.Recognition;  
using System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar;  
  
namespace SampleRecognition  
{  
  class Program  
  {  
    static void Main(string[] args)  
  
    // Initialize an instance of the in-process recognizer.  
    {  
      using (SpeechRecognitionEngine recognizer =  
         new SpeechRecognitionEngine(new System.Globalization.CultureInfo("en-US")))  
      {  
  
        // Build the SrgsOneOf objects with alternative choices for the slang phrase.  
        SrgsOneOf gimme = new SrgsOneOf(  
          new string[] { "give me", "gimme", "hand me", "ha'me" });  
        SrgsOneOf the = new SrgsOneOf(new string[] { "the", "duh" });  
  
        // Build the one-of element that contains the pronunciation.  
        SrgsItem thing = new SrgsItem("thingamajig");  
        SrgsItem whatcha = new SrgsItem();  
        SrgsToken callit = new SrgsToken("whatchamacallit");  
        callit.Pronunciation = "W AE T CH AE M AE K AA L IH T";  
        whatcha.Add(callit);  
        SrgsOneOf what = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {thing, whatcha});  
  
        // Create the rule from the SrgsOneOf objects.  
        SrgsRule slangRule = new SrgsRule("slang", gimme, the, what);  
  
        // Build an SrgsDocument object from the rule and set the phonetic alphabet.  
        SrgsDocument tokenPron = new SrgsDocument(slangRule);  
        tokenPron.PhoneticAlphabet = SrgsPhoneticAlphabet.Ups;  
  
        // Create a Grammar object from the SrgsDocument and load it to the recognizer.  
        Grammar g_Slang = new Grammar(tokenPron);  
        g_Slang.Name = ("Slang Pronunciation");  
        recognizer.LoadGrammarAsync(g_Slang);  
  
        // Configure recognizer input.  
        recognizer.SetInputToDefaultAudioDevice();  
  
        // Attach a handler for the SpeechRecognized event.  
        recognizer.SpeechRecognized +=   
          new EventHandler<SpeechRecognizedEventArgs>(recognizer_SpeechRecognized);  
  
        // Start asynchronous recognition.  
        recognizer.RecognizeAsync();  
        Console.WriteLine("Starting asynchronous recognition...");  
  
        // Keep the console window open.  
        Console.ReadLine();  
      }  
    }  
  
    // Handle the SpeechRecognized event.  
    static void recognizer_SpeechRecognized(object sender, SpeechRecognizedEventArgs e)  
    {  
      Console.WriteLine("Recognized phrase: " + e.Result.Text);  
      Console.WriteLine("Confidence: " + e.Result.Confidence);  
      Console.WriteLine("  Word summary: ");  
      foreach (RecognizedWordUnit word in e.Result.Words)  
      {  
        Console.WriteLine(  
          "    Lexical form ({1})" +  
          " Pronunciation ({0})" +  
          " Confidence ({2})",  
          word.Pronunciation, word.LexicalForm, word.Confidence);  
      }  
    }  
  }  
}  
  
```
